From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joey Arhar <jarhar@chromium.org>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 08:56:57 -0700
Subject: Add CHECK for in progress moves in selectedcontent cloning

A recent change should have made sure the selectedcontent element
doesn't make any DOM changes during a move operation, and this patch
just adds an additional CHECK next to some DCHECKs as a good measure to
make sure this can't happen.

Bug: 517345069, 458113204
Change-Id: I74dbb5914b2de15ca8a84c425bc6e7222da9655e
Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/7883677
Reviewed-by: David Grogan <dgrogan@chromium.org>
Commit-Queue: David Grogan <dgrogan@chromium.org>
Reviewed-by: Joey Arhar <jarhar@chromium.org>
Auto-Submit: Joey Arhar <jarhar@chromium.org>
Cr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/main@{#1638510}

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/forms/html_selected_content_element.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/forms/html_selected_content_element.cc
index affc49fd906abfc08b8c4cc2bf50150619b9814e..2486f24b71b4a978f75695e6c77cfffbbf92f582 100644
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/forms/html_selected_content_element.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/forms/html_selected_content_element.cc
@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@
 
 #include "third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/forms/html_selected_content_element.h"
 
+#include "third_party/blink/renderer/core/dom/document.h"
 #include "third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/forms/html_option_element.h"
 #include "third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/forms/html_select_element.h"
 
@@ -18,6 +19,10 @@ void HTMLSelectedContentElement::CloneContentsFromOptionElement(
     return;
   }
 
+  if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::SelectedcontentSpecEnabled()) {
+    CHECK(!GetDocument().StatePreservingAtomicMoveInProgress());
+  }
+
   VectorOf<Node> nodes;
   if (option) {
     for (Node& child : NodeTraversal::ChildrenOf(*option)) {
